      <div class="section__header" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem"><h2 style="color:#FEC700">Plan your visit to the pools</h2></div>
      <div class="service-cards"><div class="service-card"><div style="font-size:2.5rem">🎟️</div><p class="service-card__title">Prices 2026</p><p class="service-card__desc">Adult admission $220 MXN includes access to pools, grottoes, river, and canyon.</p><a href="/en/prices/" class="btn">See rates</a></div><div class="service-card"><div style="font-size:2.5rem">🕐</div><p class="service-card__title">Best time to visit</p><p class="service-card__desc">Weekdays early in the morning. On weekends it fills up before 10 AM.</p><a href="/en/how-to-get-here/" class="service-card__cta">How to get here →</a></div><div class="service-card"><div style="font-size:2.5rem">👟</div><p class="service-card__title">Recommended footwear</p><p class="service-card__desc">Water shoes with grip. The rock stairs between pools can be slippery.</p><a href="/en/blog/what-to-bring-to-tolantongo/" class="service-card__cta">What to bring →</a></div><div class="service-card"><div style="font-size:2.5rem">📸</div><p class="service-card__title">Best photo view</p><p class="service-card__desc">The highest pool at sunset, with the canyon as backdrop. Bring waterproof protection for your camera.</p></div></div>
